---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout title="ProjectForge | Travis Wooley" active="projects">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="eyebrow">Case Study</div>

    <div class="hero-grid">
      <div>
        <h1>ProjectForge — Technical Program Management Platform</h1>

        <h2>A local-first portfolio prototype for managing product engineering programs, industrial manufacturing projects, stage-gate execution, launch readiness, cross-functional ownership, risk, procurement visibility, file vault records, activity threads, and executive status reporting.</h2>

        <div class="badge-row">
          <span class="tag">React</span>
          <span class="tag">TypeScript</span>
          <span class="tag">Vite</span>
          <span class="tag">IndexedDB</span>
          <span class="tag">Local-First</span>
          <span class="tag">Stage-Gate TPM</span>
          <span class="tag">Risk Management</span>
          <span class="tag">Launch Readiness</span>
          <span class="tag">File Vault</span>
          <span class="tag">AI Decision-Support</span>
        </div>

        <p class="hero-text">
          ProjectForge is a completed high-fidelity portfolio prototype designed to demonstrate how technical program management can be organized around realistic engineering and industrial execution workflows without implying a production-ready cloud platform.
        </p>

        <div class="hero-buttons">
          <a href="#walkthrough" class="button primary">View Product Walkthrough</a>
          <a href="/projects" class="button secondary">Back to Projects</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-visual">
        <img src="/images/ProjectForge/PFDashboard.png" alt="ProjectForge operations command center dashboard" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="quick-facts">
    <div class="fact-card">
      <h3>Status</h3>
      <p>High-Fidelity Portfolio Prototype</p>
    </div>

    <div class="fact-card">
      <h3>Purpose</h3>
      <p>Technical Program Management for Engineering and Industrial Execution</p>
    </div>

    <div class="fact-card">
      <h3>Core Workflows</h3>
      <p>Portfolio • Intake • Phase Gates • Tasks • Risks • RACI • Readiness • Procurement • File Vault • Reports</p>
    </div>

    <div class="fact-card">
      <h3>Data Model</h3>
      <p>Local-first IndexedDB persistence with localStorage fallback and JSON backup/export concepts</p>
    </div>

    <div class="fact-card">
      <h3>Focus</h3>
      <p>Engineering Operations, Technical Program Management, Manufacturing Launch, Cross-Functional Execution</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="overview">
    <h2>Overview</h2>

    <div class="card">
      <p>
        ProjectForge is a local-first Technical Program Management platform designed to coordinate complex engineering and industrial programs from intake through execution, risk control, launch readiness, and sustaining handoff.
      </p>
      <p>
        The prototype centers on realistic TPM workflows including project intake and chartering, portfolio visibility, stage-gate execution, task and milestone tracking, risk management, stakeholder and RACI ownership, budget and procurement visibility, launch readiness, local file vault records, activity threads, executive reporting, and AI-assisted decision support.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Problem</h2>

    <div class="card">
      <p>
        Engineering and manufacturing initiatives often depend on disconnected spreadsheets, emails, shared folders, meeting notes, procurement trackers, informal status updates, and manually maintained file repositories.
      </p>
      <p>
        That fragmentation creates gaps in accountability, launch readiness, risk visibility, stakeholder alignment, evidence control, and executive reporting.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Solution</h2>

    <div class="card">
      <p>
        ProjectForge centralizes technical program execution into a single command center where stakeholders can track a portfolio of programs, intake new charters, manage stage gates, assign tasks, log risks, monitor readiness, review procurement exposure, register project files, publish coordination notes, generate status reports, and use decision-support insights.
      </p>
      <p>
        The experience is positioned as a thoughtfully designed local-first product concept for technical program management rather than a generalized task app or production SaaS platform.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

