  <section>
    <h2>Local-First Architecture</h2>

    <div class="card">
      <p>
        ProjectForge was designed with browser-local persistence so project records, tasks, risks, readiness items, procurement records, file metadata, activity notes, comments, and configuration data can remain available after refresh.
      </p>
      <p>
        JSON export and import support backup, migration, and archival snapshots. Future architecture concepts include selectable local-machine folder storage, mapped network-drive storage, OneDrive or Google Drive synced folder backup, a desktop app wrapper using Tauri or Electron, and team backends using PostgreSQL, Supabase, Firebase, or similar services.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Simulated Enterprise Integration Boundary</h2>

    <div class="disclaimer-card">
